So last night I finally started setting #goals and figuring up some numbers for my store. If you've always blindly listed and are a little unsure of how to make your monthly goals happen, like I was, then I strongly encourage you to do this as well! @suzanneawells has a great tutorial for this on her blog that walks you through step by step. Now I know my average sale price per item,  the percentage of my inventory that sells every month,  and how many listings I need to get to my next goal! I was a little shocked to see that I only profit around 45% of my total sales (that includes shipping amounts) so that's another goal,  to up that number somehow! Focusing on PROFIT not gross! 😊 Goodluck to you!

DOES THIS MAKE SENSE TO YOU? 🤔
-
Alright. I messed up. I didn’t post for about a week on my Instagram account. All of my friends probably deserted me and I lost all the followers I used to have…
-
NOT. There are things in life that truly matter, and there are things in life that truly don’t. Instagram and growing a huge Instagram following (while fun and worthwhile) is one of the things that doesn’t.
-
There was a time when I would have freaked out about having lost my streak of posting consistency. But I realize now that the more important thing is that I post not just to POST but to SAY SOMETHING. The reality is is that I haven’t had the time or inclination to post recently, but when I decided that I did I couldn’t freak out about the time that I didn’t.
-
Keep your eyes on the bigger picture, people. Focus on the destination and ignore the stumbling blocks along the way. They will always be there. The big difference between successes and failures is that the successes will get up and keep going after roadblocks and failures will sit and mope and procrastinate instead of doing something about it.
